<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>download</code> attribute on <a href="/docs/elements/native/a/"><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></a> and <code>&lt;area&gt;</code> elements tells the browser to download the linked resource as a file instead of navigating to it. Without this attribute, the browser decides based on the MIME type — PDFs might open in a viewer, images display inline, and HTML navigates.</p>
<p>When a value is provided, it serves as the suggested filename for the download. The user can still change the name in the save dialog.</p>

<h2>Values</h2>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Usage</th><th>Behavior</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>download</code> (no value)</td><td>Download the file using the filename from the URL</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>download="name.ext"</code></td><td>Suggest a custom filename for the download</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/a/"><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></a>, <code>&lt;area&gt;</code></p>

